@103760 = ~Light Breeze~
@103761 = ~At first glance, this club appears ordinary, but closer inspection reveals to the keen eye the rows of individual runes that girdle its hilt. The thief can also note the excellent balance of this weapon.

The club was enchanted in ancient times at the behest of a Shadow Thieves guild master for one of his loyal - and wealthy - protgs. While being a rather powerful weapon on one hand, it also muffles the sounds around the thief when he sneaks up on his target to send him into a deep knockout. The last thing many opponents feel before they lose consciousness is a slight puff of air from the club being brought over their heads, for which it was quickly dubbed "Light Breeze".

Unfortunately, as is often the case in such matters, a protg once failed to live up to the guild master's expectations, and on a dark night that weapon led to his death in his own bed. His wife, sleeping beside him, heard nothing.

What path this weapon traveled until it fell into your hands is a story you do not wish to know.

